From 99ac60903fa15d858f1b7532824e5f332a1fad5b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@becurious.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 13:32:53 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Car capacity %, unplaced diagnosis, and cross-car pickup
 visibility
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Car capacity: each car column header now shows a filled/total slots
  count with a color-coded progress bar (green <70%, amber 70-90%,
  red ≥90%) so supervisors instantly see which cars have room.
- Unplaced diagnosis: pool cards for students that couldn't be
  auto-scheduled show a yellow ⚠ banner explaining why (teacher
  inactive, no car for branch, teacher at daily max, all slots full).
- Cross-car pickups: when a student is dropped by one car but picked
  up by another, both columns now show clear indicators — the drop
  card says "🔄 Car X picks up" and the pickup slot in Car X shows
  "🔄 Dropped by Car Y — this car picks up [name]".

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
